			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Sky Shrine Cobalt Scar Key Quest<a name="23875"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 25 04 2:12 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Jindl:
<br />

<br />
Don't even try it.  I did on 3 separate occasions (check out my rant).  Even though Wenglakks is indifferent to you, the Storm Giant Wizard staring at him isn't.  So once the Storm Giant aggros, Wenglakks starts beating on you.
<br />

<br />
I tried having a friend with good giant faction hail the storm giant, but he kept looking at Wenglakks.  What I did (after creating an OGRE warrior who worships Rallos Zek) was sit and watch him while I was doing something else.
<br />

<br />
What I found out was that at 11pm (game time) on one day of the week (this is the tricky part, I think the day is reset with server resets) he walks out of the building toward EW, down the tunnel and then makes a left going into the building with the giant merchants.  
<br />

<br />
When he is going down this hall, he is alone and you can do the turn-in.  He won't stop walking though, so be aware of that and keep up with him so your trade window will not close.
<br />

<br />
I didn't see your level, but once you get the 2.5 min selo's at 49, it was a LOT easier since you could refresh it, zone in Kael, put invis up and still have 2+ min of speed.
<br />

<br />
Oh, btw, did you know you can get to CS by going from GD to Plane of Mischief to CS?  VERY easy, you just have to be level 46 or 47.  You zone in, put up invis, then start clicking trees until you hit the one that ports you to CS (underwater).
<br />

<br />
Good Luck to you!
<br />

<br />
Badji</span></td>
